In luce Asiae, ‘in the broad daylight of the Province of Asia.’ ‘ Asia' in Cicero's time meant that part of Asia Minor which had been the Kingdom of Pergamus, and which was the first Province which the Romans got possession of in the Continent of Asia. This is the meaning of Asia in the Acts of the Apostles. Its boundaries varied at different times. The governor of the Province resided at Ephesus.

87. Itineribus, ‘progresses.' The Roman governors made their pro- gresses through their Provinces at the expense of the provincials‚ and often put them to great cost.
